If you intend to compile the Sept CACM cryptogram solver with the Borland 
C++ 4.0 compiler for MS-DOS, you need to increase the default stack size 
-- 4K bytes in not enough. Somewhere in your global variable declarations 
include the statement

    extern unsigned _stklen = 8*1024;

to give the program an 8K byte stack size.

